THIS AINT A REWRITE, PEOPLE


27 Jun 2018 01:58






I am not mentally ready for this

So this is the most ambitious thing I have ever been involved in.

Some background on how this happened: Ages ago, back in 3K, I had an idea to write an article about the sun protecting the solar system from some sort of looming threat. This fell through (IRL issues, growing to dislike the idea, trying and failing to do another draft). Flash forward to January/February. Rimple is holding a draftswap contest. One person gives an incomplete draft to a random user in the contest, said user finishes a complete draft, and you get a draft to complete as well.

I decided to go put my 3K draft in and Varaxous got it. From here on we began a grueling writing process, with a lot of stuff changed, modified, and cut as it went on. Then other events happened. Jamcon, Doomcon, other articles. I told Varaxous we'd save it for later, to wait for some more crit, then it fell back into drafting limbo.

Then the original 1548 was deleted.

We realized the opportunity to put an article about a star in a slot previously about a (very different) star and scrambled to get it ready for posting.

So here it is now. I think it is far from perfect but hey, I'm fairly happy with how it's turned out.

Also, to reiterate, since a lot of people don't seem to have noticed,

THIS IS NOT A REWRITE.  THIS IS IN NO WAY RELATED TO THE ORIGINAL SCP-1548. 

Hope people enjoy this.





