27 Jun 2018 06:26






Ok so, this SCP does a lot of things right. A lot of stories-as-SCPs forget there's a core SCP there and get lost on some weird tangent and while this is long and has one of the most ridiculous scopes of any article I've read it still manages to flow pretty well for my tastes.

The references to other SCPs and how they're effected by the events here are a nice touch too, though perhaps overdone just a bit.

My biggest complaint though is that there seems to be a central bit of overarching lore that I'm not really familiar with or sure where to start on. It works well enough on its own as a story about extradimensional horrors devouring the universe and a possibly living sun trying to fight them off, but I kept getting the impression that there was a wink and a nudge to some reference I was supposed to get and just don't and that sensation irks me.

Still, +1.







